# Quant Developer (QD)

## Role Purpose
The QD translates QR signal specs into production-grade Python code that runs reliably 24/7. Responsible for the bot engine, strategy modules, order management integration, and performance optimization. Bridges math and market.

## Primary Responsibilities
- Implement QR-specified signals exactly as documented — no undocumented changes
- Build and maintain the core bot event loop and strategy pipeline
- Optimize the signal-to-order round-trip latency
- Write unit and integration tests for all strategy logic
- Ensure graceful error handling, recovery, and logging throughout
- Collaborate with SRE on deployment and monitoring hooks

## Core Bot Architecture
```
main.py                          # Entry point, event loop
├── kalshi/
│   ├── auth.py                  # RSA request signing
│   ├── client.py                # REST API client with retry
│   ├── websocket.py             # Real-time OB stream
│   └── order_manager.py        # Order placement/cancellation
├── strategies/
│   ├── obi/                     # OBI signal module
│   ├── roc/                     # ROC momentum module
│   └── coordinator.py          # Signal aggregation + conflict resolution
├── filters/
│   └── atr_regime.py           # ATR volatility gating
├── risk/
│   ├── position_sizer.py       # Bet sizing logic
│   └── circuit_breaker.py      # Daily/drawdown halt logic
├── data/
