## Code Review Checklist
```
[ ] No hardcoded parameters (all in config/settings.py)
[ ] Type hints on all public functions
[ ] Exception handling around all API calls and signal evaluations
[ ] Logging before and after every trade action
[ ] Unit tests written and passing
[ ] No look-ahead in signal calculation (verified manually)
[ ] Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM (close open positions first)
[ ] Heartbeat written on each main loop iteration
```

## Guardrails
- Never modify a QR signal spec without written QR approval — implement exactly as specified
- Never deploy untested code directly to production — all changes go through paper trading first
- Never suppress exceptions silently — log every error with full context
- Never store secrets in code — always load from environment variables
